<subSubSection id="B11C7D983CECD241CC7FC9823D633593" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="4236348796F483885C77B62909C6856D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B06C43D342C36E94F8B5EAFC067ED152" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">
European. The species was described from Czech Republic (
<bibRefCitation id="5A8177B298B37666B49087615B59CB52" author="Sevcik, J." journalOrPublisher="Casopis Slezskeho zemskeho muzea, Serie A, Vedy prirodni (Opava)" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" pagination="97 - 105" title="Fifty species of fungus gnats (Diptera: Mycetophilidae) new for the Czech Republic and / or Slovakia, including a new species of Allodia Winnertz" volume="48" year="1999">
<normalizedToken id="01EC450167EDEB24344485E207148901" originalValue="Ševčík">Sevcik</normalizedToken>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
), and has been recorded from Sweden (north, south, 
<bibRefCitation id="68C53B104582E37ACA173781DF87F702" author="Kjaerandsen, J." journalOrPublisher="Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution, Supplement" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" pagination="1 - 165" title="Annotated checklist of fungus gnats from Sweden (Diptera: Bolitophilidae, Diadocidiidae, Ditomyiidae, Keroplatidae and Mycetophilidae)" volume="65" year="2007">Kjaerandsen et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
), Russian Karelia (
<bibRefCitation id="FA0244CAE736E1CC89CAAA6A9BF46402" author="Polevoi, A. V." journalOrPublisher="Karelian Research Centre, Russian Academy of Sciences, Petrozavodsk" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" title="Fungus gnats (Diptera: Bolitophilidae, Ditomyiidae, Keroplatidae, Diadocidiidae, Mycetophilidae) in Karelia." year="2000">Polevoi 2000</bibRefCitation>
) and Finland (south). Here reported from North Finland.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A53957EBF822CD15E5A00598CA28492A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="2D3FBBCFB4F24039146C9AFB9CCA157C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">Ecology</paragraph>
<paragraph id="831B5144EAD51CE60A8B66705EA9CBB7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">
Sampling sites are a headwater stream and a swampy lake shore. Immature stages are unknown. Related species 
<taxonomicName id="744D699BDAB2006EC4EB17A9B565BDAD" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Allodia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Allodia (Brachycampta) pistillata" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pistillata" subGenus="Brachycampta">Allodia (Brachycampta) pistillata</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="A837BBE5702AF267A33CBE33D6C0FF4F" originalValue="Lundström">Lundstroem</normalizedToken>
was reared by Jakovlev (
<bibRefCitation id="D30EEBAAB9D940B28CC8FFEBD433873B" author="Jakovlev, J." journalOrPublisher="Karelian Research Center, Russian Academy of Sciences, Forest Research Institute, Petrozavodsk" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" title="Palaearctic Diptera associated with fungi and myxomycetes" year="1994">Jakovlev 1994</bibRefCitation>
) from the ascomycete fungus 
<taxonomicName id="FC34D6BBD76C51BD2DB3012197974B11" class="Pezizomycetes" family="Pezizaceae" genus="Peziza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Peziza" order="Pezizales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Peziza</taxonomicName>
sp.
</paragraph>
